{"title": "Creating Sessions in Time Zones FAQ's", "body": "  Sessions are align with the provider's time zone.\nWhen looking at sessions it will display in the assigned providers' time zone NOT the viewer's time zone.\nThe appointment Book is converted to the viewer's time zone.\nCalendar show practice hours which are based on the primary users' time zone.\nWhen patients are viewing appointments from the MediRecords App: they are viewing it in their local time, and these appointments are then converted to the provider's time zone.\nThe appointment Widget is dictated by the primary users' time zone.\n  Community Sessions & Appointment Types"}